    <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Family Planning & Contraception</h1>
    <p class="text-center mb-5">Understanding your options for preventing or planning pregnancy.</p>
    
    <div class="row align-items-center">
      <div class="col-lg-6">
        <h2>What is Family Planning?</h2>
        <p>Family planning involves making informed decisions about whether and when to have children. It includes contraception to prevent pregnancy and fertility awareness to help achieve pregnancy when desired.</p>
        <p>Effective family planning allows individuals and couples to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Take control of their reproductive health</li>
          <li>Plan pregnancies according to their life circumstances</li>
          <li>Space children for optimal maternal and child health</li>
          <li>Prevent unintended pregnancies</li>
          <li>Reduce the need for unsafe abortions</li>
          <li>Lower the risk of pregnancy complications</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Every woman has unique needs and preferences when it comes to family planning. Understanding all available options helps you make the best choice for your situation.</p>
      </div>
